Businesses Supplier Development Programme.  Platform Capital launches in SA to help grow the local SMME sector5 Apr 2022From youth development perspective, the Umsobomvu Youth Fund and the National Youth Service have already been established for the purpose of helping our youth set up, expand and develop their businesses by teaching them essential business skills. Youth Advisory Centres (YACs) have been established around the country, providing walk-in facilities for youth to receive information, training and referrals. Funding can be facilitated through agencies like Khula Enterprise Finance and the South African Micro-Finance Apex Fund, as they all have their own criteria processes, service providers to ensure that we achieve the desired trickle-down effect towards beneficiation and job creation. Support structures for growthFunctionally, we need a more defined, structured process around entrepreneurial establishment and growth in the country, such as the establishment of more entrepreneurial hubs that are accessible to those who need them. All the various small business development agencies need to come together at these hubs to facilitate business support in one easily accessible location within our living spaces. In addition, business support interventions like manufacturing hubs will be critical for growth. Here, multiple businesses share access to expensive manufacturing equipment that they would not be able to achieve alone. 4 mistakes every new entrepreneur should avoidBy Banele Rewo 8 Feb 2022Educational foundationsFocusing on economic redevelopment requires the allocated funds to be properly utilised, which means starting at an educational level. To properly channel their strengths, career counselling at school needs to begin with an assessment of whether an individual is an entrepreneur or an employee. At school level, general entrepreneurial programs are required, as well as community-wide support programmes. In terms of skills development, there needs to be a rebranding campaign for blue-collar or artisanal trades. Our economy does not  need more lawyers or accountants to rebuild instead school learners need to realise that entering a trade or acquiring a critical skill that is in shortage is the best way to ensure employability and to earn a living reliably. For example, every year the government releases its list of critical skills. This is a missed opportunity for youth skills development, as we have the potential right under our noses, all we need to do is identify their potential and develop these critical skills within our own borders, by creating the necessary educational, training and support structures that help to make the youth employable while creating employment opportunities through entrepreneurial development. Trends that will shape your small business in 2022By Matthew Campbell 17 Jan 2022Developing on the right ideaWhile the government has all the right intentions with small business support and youth development, it is  going to take a lot of focus and collaboration in order to properly understand what the needs are in this sector. Without this understanding, it is simply throwing money at a problem by properly defining and appreciating what the entrepreneurial needs are. We can then start to define how entrepreneurs can best be developed to encourage employment which will in turn have the consequence of creating youth employment opportunities, for which the youth need to be adequately trained, equipped and skilled in order to be employable.